<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1023,1193]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,540,1023,1050]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Record as epibiont on ostracods:</emphasis>
It lives on the external surface of the shell of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Jurine, 1820)" baseAuthorityName="Jurine" baseAuthorityYear="1820" box="[1049,1436,1024,1051]" class="Ostracoda" family="Cyprididae" genus="Cypria" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Podocopida" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ophthalmica">
<emphasis box="[1049,1273,1024,1051]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Cypria ophthalmica</emphasis>
(Jurine, 1820)
</taxonomicName>
and prefers the region near its rim from a natural, eutrophic pond in a forest (“Hauptsmoorwald”) east of Bamberg, Northern 
<collectingRegion box="[259,349,1096,1122]" country="Germany" name="Bayern" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Bavaria</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[360,464,1096,1122]" name="Germany" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Germany</collectingCountry>
and also from Kreuzschuher Bach (Aurach, Regnitz, Main) west of Bamberg, 
<collectingRegion box="[1342,1432,1096,1122]" country="Germany" name="Bayern" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Bavaria</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[151,255,1132,1158]" name="Germany" pageId="6" pageNumber="23">Germany</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Schodel, H." box="[270,430,1132,1158]" pageId="6" pageNumber="23" pagination="107 - 128" refId="ref8001" refString="Schodel, H. (2004) New and rare epizoic peritrichs (Protozoa, Ciliophora) on ostracods (Arthropoda, Crustacea) with description of a new family, Bezedniellidae fam. nov. Lauterbomia, 49, 107 - 128." type="journal article" year="2004">Schödel 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
